# Connect to bandit3
ssh bandit3@bandit.labs.overthewire.org -p 2220

# List visible files and directories
ls

# Change to the inhere directory
cd inhere

# List files (won't show hidden files)
ls

# List all files including hidden ones
ls -a

# Alternative: ls -la for detailed listing
ls -la

# Read the hidden file
cat .hidden


Solution
Use ls -a to show hidden files. The file .hidden contains the password.
Key Learnings

Hidden files concept (files starting with .)
ls -a flag to show all files including hidden ones
ls -la for detailed listing with permissions
Directory navigation with cd
Understanding file visibility rules in Linux
